               <provenance>Additio 1 mentiones ʾabuna Gabra ʾIyasus as the donor. His name was inserted in the
                     supplication formulas in Text I, in hand b (3ra,
                     5rb, 13va, 14ra, 14rb, 48ra, 49ra, 81ra etc.) alonside the names of his
                     relatives: his wife Ḍädalä Māryām (6va, 26ra,
                     49ra, 54vb, 81ra), his father Mazgaba Śǝllāse (on 9rb. 11ra, 11rb, 11vb, 12rb, 54rb, 81ra, etc.), his mother Walatta
                     Madḫǝn (8ra, 59ra, 61va, 81ra), his children Takla
                     Māryām (8va, 9vb, 11vb, 13ra, 14vb, 81ra, etc.)
                     and Walatta Śǝllāse (23vb, 29ra, 33ra, 68ra,
                     74ra, 81ra).</provenance></history>
